<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-04-0450 </DOCNO><TEXT>The share of natural gas in the world energy supply increased from 250million tce (10%) in 1950 to 2.2 billion tce (20%) in 1986. Natural gasthus is third among the world's energy sources. The article discussesthe contribution of natural gas to the world energy supply, the worldgas reserves, production, consumption, and sales. The perspectives ofnatural gas consumption in the world and in important OECD regions arediscussed as well as the trends of the world energy market. Natural gasis defined here as comprising, pure natural gas (90% methane) and accompanyinggas (mixtures of C1 to C4). (MOS).</TEXT></DOC>